        <article class="lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-3 font-sans text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-300 space-y-32">
            
            <!-- 1. CONTEXT -->
            <section id="context" class="reveal">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif italic text-white mb-8">01. Context</h2>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    Booking.com has arguably the largest inventory in the world. But in 2023, this strength became a weakness. Users were spending hours filtering through 500+ options, often leaving without booking due to <strong>decision fatigue</strong>.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    The goal was clear: <strong class="text-white">Stop users from "Searching" and start helping them "Choose."</strong>
                </p>
                
                <div class="bg-[#0f172a] border-l-4 border-[#829DF1] p-6 rounded-r-xl my-8">
                    <p class="text-white italic">"The increased time and page visits on Booking.com are likely due to indecisive exploration rather than engagement."</p>
                    <span class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mt-2 block">— Data Analysis Insight</span>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- 2. RESEARCH: Indecisive Exploration -->
            <section id="research" class="reveal">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif italic text-white mb-8">02. Research & Insights</h2>
                <p class="mb-12">
                    During secondary research, we analyzed traffic patterns. The data showed a clear distinction between "Focused" and "Indecisive" behaviors when comparing with competitors.
                </p>
                
                <!-- DATA SYNTHESIS LAYOUT -->
                <div class="space-y-8">
                    
                    <!-- Data Screenshot -->
                    <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-white/10 shadow-2xl group relative">
                        <img src="img/booking-com_case_study/engagement-analysis.webp" alt="Data Analysis Chart" class="w-full h-auto object-cover opacity-90 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">
                        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-[#020617] to-transparent opacity-30 pointer-events-none"></div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Horizontal Layout for Insights -->
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                        
                        <!-- Focused Card (Glassmorphic) -->
                        <div class="relative group overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#0f172a] p-8 transition-all duration-500 hover:border-green-500/30 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_-10px_rgba(34,197,94,0.2)]">
                            <div class="absolute -right-10 -top-10 h-32 w-32 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 blur-[50px] transition-all duration-700 group-hover:bg-green-500/20"></div>
                            <div class="relative z-10">
                                <div class="mb-4 flex items-center justify-between">
                                    <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-white">MakeMyTrip</h4>
                                    <span class="rounded-full border border-green-500/30 bg-green-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-400">Focused</span>
                                </div>
                                <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
                                    Users visit fewer pages but spend quality time reading details. This indicates <span class="text-white font-medium">efficient decision making</span>.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Indecisive Card (Glassmorphic) -->
                        <div class="relative group overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#0f172a] p-8 transition-all duration-500 hover:border-red-500/30 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_-10px_rgba(239,68,68,0.2)]">
                            <div class="absolute -right-10 -top-10 h-32 w-32 rounded-full bg-red-500/10 blur-[50px] transition-all duration-700 group-hover:bg-red-500/20"></div>
                            <div class="relative z-10">
                                <div class="mb-4 flex items-center justify-between">
                                    <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-white">Booking.com</h4>
                                    <span class="rounded-full border border-red-500/30 bg-red-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-red-400">Indecisive</span>
                                </div>
                                <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
                                    Users visit significantly more pages with high bounce rates. This signals <span class="text-white font-medium">choice paralysis</span>.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                </div>

                <p class="mt-12 text-sm text-muted border-t border-white/10 pt-6">
                    This data validated <strong>Hick's Law</strong>: The time it takes to make a decision increases with the number and complexity of choices.
                </p>
            </section>

             <!-- 3. PROCESS & METHODOLOGIES (Restored) -->
             <section id="methodologies" class="reveal">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif italic text-white mb-8">03. Process & Methodologies</h2>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    To validate our hypotheses within the 48-hour constraint, we employed a lean UX methodology focusing on rapid discovery and validation.
                </p>

                <div class="space-y-8">
                    
                    <!-- Method 1 -->
                    <div class="bg-surface border border-border p-6 rounded-xl flex gap-6 items-start">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#0f172a] border border-[#829DF1]/30 flex items-center justify-center text-[#829DF1] shrink-0">
                            <i class="fas fa-search-plus text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-xl text-white font-medium mb-2">User Engagement Analysis</h3>
                            <p class="text-sm text-muted">
                                We didn't just look at "bounce rate." We looked at the <strong>Pages per Session</strong> vs. <strong>Conversion</strong> ratio. High pages/session with low conversion is the hallmark of a confused user, not an engaged one. This directed us to solve for "guidance" rather than "more content."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Method 2 -->
                    <div class="bg-surface border border-border p-6 rounded-xl flex gap-6 items-start">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#0f172a] border border-[#829DF1]/30 flex items-center justify-center text-[#829DF1] shrink-0">
                            <i class="fas fa-flask text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-xl text-white font-medium mb-2">Remote Usability Testing</h3>
                            <p class="text-sm text-muted">
                                We conducted rapid 15-minute zoom sessions with 3 participants. We gave them a vague goal: "Find a hotel in Andaman for a weekend." We observed their screen interaction—specifically noting <strong>mouse pauses</strong>, <strong>back-button usage</strong>, and <strong>tab switching</strong> to identify friction points.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </section>


            <!-- 4. THE SOLUTION (Linear Layout) -->
            <section id="solution" class="reveal">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif italic text-white mb-12">04. The Solution</h2>
                <p class="mb-12">
                    We shifted the strategy from **Search-First** to **Discovery-First**. By leveraging past user data, we auto-curated a "Recommended for You" feed.
                </p>

                <div class="space-y-24">
                    
                    <!-- Step 1: Home Page -->
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
                        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2 rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden shadow-2xl bg-black">
                            <img src="img/ui/UI-01.png" alt="Home Page Personalization" class="w-full h-auto object-contain">
                        </div>
                        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2 pt-4">
                            <span class="text-[#829DF1] font-bold text-lg block mb-2">01. "Just For You" Section</span>
                            <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
                                Instead of a cold search bar, returning users see a horizontal scroll of hotels matching their past budget and style preferences immediately upon login.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Step 2: Context Tags -->
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
                        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2 rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden shadow-2xl bg-black">
                            <img src="img/ui/UI-02.png" alt="Context Tags" class="w-full h-auto object-contain">
                        </div>
                        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2 pt-4">
                            <span class="text-[#829DF1] font-bold text-lg block mb-2">02. Contextual Reasoning</span>
                            <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
                                Cards explicitly state <em>why</em> this is recommended (e.g., "Similar to your stay in Goa") to build trust in the algorithm.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Step 3: Search Results -->
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start">
                        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2 rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden shadow-2xl bg-black">
                            <img src="img/ui/UI-03.png" alt="Visual Disruption" class="w-full h-auto object-contain">
                        </div>
                        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2 pt-4">
                            <span class="text-[#829DF1] font-bold text-lg block mb-2">03. Visual Disruption</span>
                            <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
                                Recommended properties break the grid. They are larger and have a distinct border, visually separating "Signal" from "Noise."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- 5. EVOLUTION: Iteration & Refinement -->
            <section id="evolution" class="reveal">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif italic text-white mb-8">05. Evolution & Iteration</h2>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    The design didn't happen in a vacuum. We iterated from low-fidelity wireframes to high-fidelity prototypes, refining the information architecture at each step based on usability testing.
                </p>

                 <!-- PROGRESSIVE SLIDER (With JS for Mouse Drag) -->
                 <div class="w-full overflow-hidden my-12 cursor-grab active:cursor-grabbing" id="slider-container">
                    <h3 class="text-xl text-white font-medium mb-6 pl-1">Visual Progression</h3>
                    <div class="flex overflow-x-auto gap-6 snap-x snap-mandatory no-scrollbar pb-4" id="slider">
                        
                        <!-- Iteration 1: Wireframe -->
                        <div class="snap-center shrink-0 w-[85%] md:w-[600px] aspect-[4/3] bg-surface rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden group relative pointer-events-none">
